 <title>Verizon App Challenge Best in Nation Winners Announced</title>
 <link>http://explore.appinventor.mit.edu/blogs/karen/2016/02</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden view-mode-rss&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;http://appchallenge.tsaweb.org/sites/appchallenge.tsaweb.org/files/press-room/BestNation-pdf%20for%20website1-flat.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Best in Nation Finalists&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=&quot;http://appchallenge.tsaweb.org/Verizon&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Verizon App Challenge&lt;/a&gt; were announced today. Congratulations to all the winners, not only of the Best in Nation, but &lt;a href=&quot;http://appchallenge.tsaweb.org/sites/appchallenge.tsaweb.org/files/press-room/BestState-2016%20pdf%20for%20website-flat.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Best in State&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;http://appchallenge.tsaweb.org/sites/appchallenge.tsaweb.org/files/press-room/BestRegion-2016-pdf%20for%20website-flat.pdf&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Best in Region&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Middle school and high school teams from around the nation developed ideas for apps that addressed a need in their school or community. They wrote essays describing their design process, their app’s functionality, and its potential impact or outcome. In addition, each team produced a 3 minute video describing the app and its impact. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Best in Nation Team Winners receive a $15,000 grant to build the app from their winning design and to enhance STEM education at their schools or site. MIT App Inventor Master Trainers will be working with the nine national finalists in person and virtually to develop their app over the next few months. Winning teams will present their apps at the TSA National Conference in Nashville, TN, in June. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;section class=&quot;field field-name-field-genre field-type-list-text field-label-above view-mode-rss&quot;&gt;&lt;h2 class=&quot;field-label&quot;&gt;Genre:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;Blog&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/section&gt;</description>
